The `DotGlobeHero` component is a React component designed to display a captivating, animated globe background. It utilizes `react-three-fiber` to render a 3D globe within a full-screen container, overlaying any provided children content.

## Key Exports

- `DotGlobeHero`: The main React component for rendering the globe hero. It accepts `DotGlobeHeroProps`.
- `DotGlobeHeroProps`: An interface defining the properties that can be passed to the `DotGlobeHero` component.

## Props

### `DotGlobeHeroProps`

- `rotationSpeed` (optional, number): Controls the speed at which the globe rotates. Defaults to `0.005`.
- `globeRadius` (optional, number): Determines the radius of the globe. Defaults to `1`.
- `className` (optional, string): Allows for custom styling of the main container element.
- `children` (optional, React.ReactNode): Content to be displayed on top of the globe.

## Usage Example

```tsx
import { DotGlobeHero } from "@/components/ui/globe-hero";

function MyPage() {
  return (
    <DotGlobeHero rotationSpeed={0.01} globeRadius={1.5} className="text-white">
      <h1 className="text-4xl font-bold">Welcome to DocMed</h1>
      <p className="mt-2 text-lg">Your documentation starts here.</p>
    </DotGlobeHero>
  );
}

export default MyPage;
```
